images.alt: A 24-year-old elegant androgynous tomboy with a boyish shape, toned midriff, and visible flat abs, standing in a neo-brutalist sky lobby of a Zurich high-rise in 2124--its walls a fusion of recycled carbon-fiber panels and self-repairing bio-concrete, bathed in the soft glow of holographic cityscapes beyond the floor-to-ceiling windows. She wears a minimalist, tech-infused ensemble that defines 2124’s street-luxe aesthetic: a cropped, climate-adaptive top (woven from lab-grown spider silk, its surface shifting between matte black and iridescent silver to regulate temperature), paired with high-waisted, modular cargo pants made from upcycled spacecraft materials, their magnetic seams adjusting to her movements. Her ankle boots are crafted from biodegradable nano-leather, their anti-grav soles hovering just above the ground. Slung over her shoulder is the IT Bag of 2124--a sleek, geometric 'Neo-Pod' by Zurich-based label Helvetia X. The bag is crafted from self-healing polymer and embedded with a mini terrarium of extraterrestrial plants on its front panel, their bioluminescent leaves pulsing in sync with her smartwatch’s biometric readouts. The bag’s modular straps double as a portable charger for her holographic sketchpad, which floats beside her, displaying 3D renders of her latest OpenSim avatar designs. The sky lobby’s floating furniture and zero-gravity art installations reflect the clean lines of her outfit, while a fractured neon sign in the background reads 'CODE THE FUTURE' in Swiss German slang. The scene is ultra-modern yet raw: high-contrast lighting sculpts her defined abs and the architectural angles of the space, with dappled reflections from the holographic billboards outside casting dynamic shadows. The color palette is sophisticated and futuristic: gunmetal grays, electric blues, and deep greens, with hyper-detailed textures emphasizing the fusion of sustainability and cutting-edge tech.
